OL,3,CCouncil tax rise and new flood fund
OL,4,Cproposed by Leicestershire County
OL,5,CCouncil
OL,7,FThe four-year budget paints a stark
OL,8,Fpicture of rising costs, with
OL,9,Finflation and soaring demand for
OL,10,Fservices adding an extra #218 million
OL,11,Fto expenditure.
OL,13,FHowever, the council expects to bring
OL,14,Fin only #127 million in additional
OL,15,Fincome and savings, leaving a
OL,16,Fsubstantial shortfall.
OL,18,FAmong the key spending pledges is
OL,19,Fnearly #100 million extra for
OL,20,Fsupporting vulnerable children and
OL,21,Fadults.
