OL,7,FCouncil Tax will rise by 4.99%,
OL,8,Fbringing in an extra #20 million,
OL,9,Fwhich the council says is only enough
OL,10,Fto cover increases in National Living
OL,11,FWage and National Insurance, without
OL,12,Ffactoring in rising demand for
OL,13,Fservices.
OL,15,FActing council leader Councillor
OL,16,FDeborah Taylor stressed the importance
OL,17,Fof focusing on what the council can
OL,18,Fcontrol, while urging Westminster to
OL,19,Fstep up.
