OL,7,FHe defended the Council Tax increase,
OL,8,Fsaying it was necessary to avoid
OL,9,Fdeeper cuts: "No one wants to increase
OL,10,FCouncil Tax but without it, we'd have
OL,11,Fto make #20 million more savings next
OL,12,Fyear, and consultation feedback showed
OL,13,Fgood support for our proposals.
OL,15,F"Thanks to taking tough decisions and
OL,16,Fplanning ahead, we aren't at the
OL,17,Fcrisis point many other councils face.
OL,18,FBut we have reached a stage where it's
OL,19,Fvital Government tackles the big
OL,20,Fissues driving our costs head on."
